## **ğŸ”¹ Service Control Policies (SCPs) in AWS Organizations**
ğŸ“Œ SCPs are **policies that limit permissions** across AWS accounts in an Organization.  

### **ğŸ“Œ Example SCP (Deny S3 Bucket Deletion)**
```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": "s3:DeleteBucket",
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
```
ğŸ“Œ **Explanation:**  
- This SCP **prevents all accounts in the Organization from deleting S3 buckets**.  

